  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Specific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but typically include three key stages:\n\n1. Placement - Initially introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering - Conducting complex financial transactions to obscure the money's origin\n3. Integration - Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into legitimate economic activities\n\nMost legal definitions require:\n- Intentional concealment of criminal proceeds\n- Knowing the funds derive from illegal activity\n- Attempting to make funds appear legitimate\n- Engaging in financial transactions to hide the source\n\nThe precise specifics can differ between countries, but these are common core elements in legal frameworks like the US Bank Secrecy Act and international anti-money laundering regulations.\n\nWould you be interested in hearing more about specific legal definitions or international approaches to money laundering?",
